\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filipinos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Filipino people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filipinos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filipinos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yulo opened with a tumbling pass that featured a high-flying 2-1/2 double piked front somersault and rounded off the dynamic display with an astonishing 3-1/2 twisting forward somersault.\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 1153, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When he stuck his final landing, he punched the air with both fists, let out a huge roar and then saluted the hollering crowd that had leapt to their feet to applaud the virtuoso performance.\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1346, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He scored 15.000 points, edging out Tokyo champion Artem Dolgopyat of Israel by just 0.034 of a point.\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1450, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1384, \"end\": 1389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999806191224262, \"rank\": 1.937593748314991e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1418, \"end\": 1424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9994321112397809, \"rank\": 0.0005673890728594592, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Top qualifier Jake Jarman of Britain settled for third, just 0.067 of a point adrift of the gold medal spot after committing small landing errors on his tumbles.\", \"from\": 1452, \"to\": 1613, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1466, \"end\": 1470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_the_Dog\", \"score\": 0.9968808112770634, \"rank\": 0.0022413868575350522, \"text\": \"Jake\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_the_Dog\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_the_Dog\"}, {\"begin\": 1481, \"end\": 1488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9519800260227291, \"rank\": 0.050196942322779985, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the final score flashed on the big screen at Bercy Arena, Yulo, overcome with emotion, covered his face with his hands as he broke down in tears and collapsed to the ground.\", \"from\": 1615, \"to\": 1793, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Filipino athletes at the Paris Games have been promised a fully furnished, two-bedroom condominium in Taguig City if they win a gold medal.\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1934, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1897, \"end\": 1908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taguig\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Taguig City\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taguig\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taguig\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yulo said he was grateful for thereward, but that it was secondary to the world title he had just won.\", \"from\": 1936, \"to\": 2038, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's just a bonus for me.\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And this is what really matters,\\\" he said, clutching the medal around his neck.\", \"from\": 2067, \"to\": 2146, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My hard work and the people who really helped me.\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2198, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I know my success is also their success\\u2026 I am happy that I won gold.\", \"from\": 2199, \"to\": 2267, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I also won a house,\\\" he said, laughing.\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2311, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yulo, who trained for seven years in Japan due to a lack of opportunity back home, said he hoped his historic win would open the door for children in the Philippines to take up the sport.\", \"from\": 2313, \"to\": 2500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2350, \"end\": 2355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.988204999218151, \"rank\": 0.011121005464576625, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 2467, \"end\": 2478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.99999998172666, \"rank\": 1.795462944085736e-08, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Hopefully gymnastics in the country will grow,\\\" he said.- Rappler.com  How does this make you feel?\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2602, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"follow us\", \"from\": 2604, \"to\": 2613, \"entities\": []}]}"